clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the treatment of bacterial blepharitis bacterial bonjunctivitis corneal injuries corneal ulcers and meibomianitis For the prophylaxis of ocular infections following foreign body removal

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Framycetin is used for the treatment of bacterial eye infections such as conjunctivitis Framycetin is an antibiotic It is not active against fungi viruses and most kinds of anaerobic bacteria Framycetin works by binding to the bacterial 30S ribosomal subunit causing misreading of t RNA leaving the bacterium unable to synthesize proteins vital to its growth Framycetin is useful primarily in infections involving aerobic bacteria bacteria
